headline: Baxter warns hurricane disruptions at IV facility may hit financials in 2025
summary: (Reuters) -Baxter International warned on Friday that hurricane-related disruptions at its North Carolina IV solutions facility could affect its financials through early 2025.  Shares of the medical products maker fell 4.4% in morning trading.  While all manufacturing lines at the facility are expected to resume before the end of this year, the production of a key IV product will reach full capacity only in early 2025, CEO ​José Almeida said in an earnings call.
